          ISPF/PDF edit contains 2 line command that are not documented.

          First is the UC command.
          It will take data and translate it to upper-case.
          You may specify UC on a single line or UC followed by a
          number. For example, UC99 will set the next 99 lines to upper
          case. The block command is UUC, UCC or UCUC. They all work.

          Next is the LC command.
          It will take data and translate it to lower-case.
          You may specify LC on a single line or LC followed by a
          number. For example, LC99 will set the next 99 lines to lower
          case. The block command is LLC, LCC or LCLC. They all work.
